  "name": "Remove Vampirism",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/skills/blood_10.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 13th level, the vampire hunter can prevent a creature killed by a vampire from returning to life as a vampire itself. By spending 10 minutes and dousing a body with a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/equipment/goods-and-services/containers-bags-boxes-more#TOC-Vial\">vial</a>&nbsp;of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/equipment/goods-and-services/toys-games-puzzles#TOC-Holy-Water\">holy water</a>, the vampire hunter removes the infection of vampirism from a creature slain by a vampire’s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/universal-monster-rules#TOC-Blood-Drain-Ex-\">blood drain</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/e/energy-drain\">energy drain</a>&nbsp;ability, preventing it from rising as a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/monster-listings/templates/vampire/vampire-spawn\">vampire spawn</a>&nbsp;via a vampire’s create spawn ability. This effect cannot be undone with any magic weaker than a @Compendium[pf1.spells.suel7sgnztenv551]{Miracle}&nbsp;or @Compendium[pf1.spells.nnj51dwfkwd15ngj]{Wish}. If the corpse is returned to life and subsequently killed by a vampire again might it become a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/monster-listings/templates/vampire/vampire-spawn\">vampire spawn</a>.</p>"
    },
